-----------
Before run
-----------

Firefox driver should be located to the 'drivers' folder and named as 'geckodriver'.
It may be downloaded from 'https://github.com/mozilla/geckodriver/releases'.


----------------------------
How to run from command line
----------------------------

1. go to "/test/functional/" folder (where the POM file is located)
2. mvn clean test -Dsuite={suiteName}

where {suiteName} is a testNG xml profile file (existing profile files are located at "/test/functional/" folder).

E.g. "appsManagementSuite.xml" profile contains all test cases from "AppsManagementTest" suite.
"runJobGroup.xml" profile will run test cases with group = "runJob".
So in this case you should use the command "mvn clean test -Dsuite=runJobGroup.xml"
You may create other testNG profiles depending your requirements.


----------------------------
How to see reports/logs
----------------------------

The folder with full logs, screenshots and page sources: /target/debug-log/
(it can be configured in resources/settings.properties)

ReportNG report is created here: /target/surefire-reports/ (you should open "/html/index.html" file)